text: The 1988 United States presidential election in California took place on November 8, 1988. that was part of the 1988 United States presidential election. Incumbent Vice President George H. W. Bush and his running mate U.S. Senator Dan Quayle had won 47 electoral votes in the Electoral College. == References == Category:1988 United States presidential election Category:1980s in California
